{
  "texts": [
    "Metrics such as the Rand index 34 and variation of information 35 address this issue by avoiding one-to-one correspondence between predicted and reference instances.",
    "To make our framework applicable to such specific use cases, we integrated the step of choosing application-specific metrics in the main workflow (Fig. 2).",
    "Examples of such application-specific metrics can be found in related work 36, 37.",
    "Metrics Reloaded primarily provides guidance for the selection of metrics that measure some notion of the 'correctness' of an algorithm's predictions on a set of test cases.",
    "It should be noted that holistic algorithm performance assessment also includes other aspects."
  ]
}